# Auto-push every 10 commands

This project auto-pushes to `origin/main` after every **10 user prompts** via `.cursor/hooks/auto_push.py`.

## Agent behavior

- **Never commit.** Commits are made only by **katharina-brenner** manually (see rule `git-commits-by-user-only`).
- Do **not** push manually on every turn; the hook pushes automatically on every 10th completed command **if the user has already committed locally**.
- If the user explicitly asks to push, push right away regardless of the counter.
- After a manual push, mention that the auto-push counter still increments in the background.

## Counter and logs

- Counter file: `.cursor/command_counter.json` (local only, gitignored)
- Push log: `.cursor/auto_push.log`
- Remote: `https://github.com/Grimmchen68/Bioreactor-Cultured-Meat`

## Hook workflow (every agent turn end)

1. Increment command counter
2. On multiples of 10: `git fetch`, `git pull --rebase origin main`, then `git push origin main` if local commits exist
